<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870128-0029 </DOCNO><HL> Computer AssociatesSells Convertible Debt</HL><DD> 01/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CABOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><DATELINE> GARDEN CITY, N.Y.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Computer Associates International Inc. sold $100 million of 5 3/4% convertible debentures due 2012 and priced at par, said Alex. Brown andamp; Sons Inc., head underwriter.    The securities are convertible at a rate of $48.25 of debentures for each common share. Computer Associates closed at $38.625, up $1.125, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading.    The company said it will use proceeds to pay bank debt, to provide funds for possible acquisition of computer software products or related businesses, and for working capital. Computer Associates designs and markets standardized software products. </TEXT></DOC>